          "body": "When Moses comes down with the second set of tablets, *the skin of his face shone because of his speaking with Him* (34:29). The verb (*qaran*) is used only here in the OT; it means to send out rays. Moses did not know. Aaron and Israel saw and were afraid. So Moses adopted a practice — veil off before the LORD, veil on before the people, veil off again before the LORD — for the rest of his ministry (34:34-35). Paul exegetes this in 2 Corinthians 3:7-18 as the *fading* glory of the old covenant, contrasted with the *unveiled* and *transforming* glory of the new. The mediator's transient radiance points forward to the Mediator whose glory is His own (John 1:14; 17:5)."
